<div1 type="letter">

<pb facs="nei.j4c.47.13-14_0001" />

 <opener>
 <dateline>Skyrim, Nov. 20, 65</dateline>


<salute>Dear Slade:</salute>
 </opener>
<p>I'm very sorry about the Prayer Garden photo, but perhaps it would be just as well, or <hi rend="double underline">better</hi>, to use a diagram instead of a photo. In the <hi rend="underline">"Nebraska History"</hi> quarterly I'm sending you will see the Prayer Garden photo. It's good of <hi rend="underline">me</hi> but shows very little of the Garden.</p>

<p>I'd go ahead using a <hi rend="underline">clear</hi>

<pb facs="nei.j4c.47.13-14_0002"/>   

<hi rend="underline">diagram</hi>. I'm enclosing some notes on the Garden which have just now turned up among my old letters. You have most of this, but you may find something useful.</p>

<p>As for Myers, <hi rend="double underline">no argument, no telling</hi> can convince anyone who has not had a vivid psychical experience of some sort. But reading Myers <hi rend="underline">is</hi> an <hi rend="underline">event</hi> of importance <add><note type="authorial">and it <hi rend="underline">can</hi> arouse a suspicion of the truth. </note></add> It's a great book.</p>
<closer>
<salute>Affectionately</salute>
<signed>John N.</signed>
</closer>

</div1>
</body>

